# @TEAM_NAME@ — team context (bootstrap scaffold)

Team: **@TEAM_NAME@** · KV bucket: `@KV_BUCKET@` · NATS URL: `$AON_NATS_URL`

Full substrate brief (substrate model, subject taxonomy, hard rules, cycle
loop, git workflow) is served at runtime by the `aon` MCP tool
`get_role_brief()`. Call it on session start — it reads the canonical source
at `templates/role-brief.md` in the engine repo and substitutes team values.

To evolve common rules for all roles: edit
`$AON_ENGINE_DIR/templates/role-brief.md`. No re-render needed — every
agent picks up the change on their next session via `get_role_brief()`.

To discover peer capabilities at runtime: call `get_peer_cards()` MCP tool.
Returns live A2A agent cards for all team members from NATS KV — updated
each agent boot. Use this instead of static rendered briefs.

